## Comparative Summary of Arguments

| Aspect                     | Arguments for Equal Treatment                         | Arguments Against Equal Treatment                      |
|----------------------------|------------------------------------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------|
| **Biological and Cognitive** | Animals share DNA similarities and feel pain        | Humans have superior intelligence and moral agency    |
| **Moral Status**            | Sentience grants animals intrinsic moral value       | Human exceptionalism justifies different rights       |
| **Practicality**            | Ethical consistency requires extending respect       | Treating animals like humans is impractical            |
| **Impact on Humans**        | Promotes compassion and reduces suffering             | Could undermine human welfare and use of animals       |
| **Cultural/Religious Views**| Calls for respect based on shared life and sentience  | Animals created for human use according to some beliefs|

